climbs.name: Trench Connection
climbs.fa: Ed Hunsaker, Troy Mayr, Posey, Duque & Amy Sharpless, 4/88

content.description: This is the unusual looking crack on the left end of the north face. It's a good beginner lead, as there are lots of ledges to stand on & place pro. Vogel's '92 guide has it at 5.6, but it's a bit easier.Walk off the top to the west.

Climb the first crack to the right of "Trench Connection".

A few weird moves lead to easier climbing.

Variation: Do the regular start, then climb the face, just right of the crack, 5.6.

This route may have already been done. I soloed it a couple days ago, and had no information on it. If anyone knows anything about it, please inform me.

Start about eight feet right of "No Strings Attached".

Climb up face, then a right leaning seam. Move straight up for a few moves, then move right to a juggy, grey face. Climb this up to the notch to the right of "No Strings Attached".

An enjoyable, easy solo, on good rock.
content.protection: Sparse pro could be had, with small stoppers and cams.

content.description: This is the right crack, or fourth from left.
content.location: The Crow's Nest, North Face, Towers of Uncertainty, Geology Tour Road, Joshua Tree National Park

content.description:
Great varied traverse on interesting rock. Right to left (west to east) stay as low as you can.

I started as far to the right of the wall as possible, before Eating Crow, and went all the way to Trench Connection. The crux is getting around the bulge right before Trench Connection. Can get pretty highball if you want it to, tons of cool features to climb.
content.location: The north side of the wall along the base of the established routes, going right to left/ west to east.

content.description: This is the third crack from left. Guidebook incorrectly states "second from left" when I believe it should be second from right.
content.location: The Crow's Nest, North Face, Towers of Uncertainty, Geology Tour Road, Joshua Tree National Park

content.description: Climb the face between Crow's Feet and Eating Crow.  Move right almost to Eating crow to reach a thin crack (crux), which slants left across a nice face. Route finishes at top out for Crow's Feet.
content.location: The Crow's Nest, Towers of Uncertainty, Geology Tour Road, Joshua Tree National Park.
